<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFAF6A10FCE994591B18B806" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFAF6A10FCE994591B61B98C" blockId="84.[788,1382,394,820]" pageId="84" pageNumber="842">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFAF6A10FCE994591DE2B913" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1916" box="[789,994,512,545]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Histiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alienus">Histiotus alienus</taxonomicName>
has been considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFAF6A10FC56947E1A52B97A" baseAuthorityName="Philippi &amp; Landbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[938,1106,551,584]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Histiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montanus">H. montanus</taxonomicName>
, and some authors suggest that it could be an oriental form of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFAF6A10FCE9942F1DADB9A5" baseAuthorityName="Poeppig" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[789,941,630,663]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Histiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrotus">H. macrotus</taxonomicName>
. Most authors consider it a full species, but its taxonomic status is uncertain.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFAF6A10FCE9949D1B18B806" blockId="84.[788,1382,394,820]" pageId="84" pageNumber="842">
Itis known only from the holotype; specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFAF6A10FCA194B51DD0B83F" box="[861,976,748,781]" name="Uruguay" pageId="84" pageNumber="842">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
identified as 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFAF6A10FB8294B51AFCB83F" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1916" box="[1150,1276,748,781]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Histiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alienus">H. alienus</taxonomicName>
actually correspond to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFAF6A10FC2B954A1A77B806" baseAuthorityName="Philippi &amp; Landbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[983,1143,787,820]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Histiotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montanus">H. montanus</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFAF6A10FF5395601DADB868" box="[175,941,825,858]" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" type="distribution">
<caption id="90EB6676FFAF6A10FF5395601DADB868" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398174" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398174" box="[175,941,825,858]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398174/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="842" targetBox="[173,764,403,817]" targetPageId="84">
